msContents.summary: Scripture by various authors known as New Testament [n]

objectDesc.p: Papyrus, 3.3x5 (27x14), 1 extant leaf(s), 1 column(s), 2 (35) line(s) per column, 28 characters per line, written in Greek.

handDesc.handNote: 275-324 Original scribe with reformed documentary hand (4 verses).

history.provenance: Excavated 1896-1907 by Bernard Grenfell and Arthur Hunt, Egypt Exploration Society at Al Bahnasā, Miṣr from a garbage dump.
Loaned to University of Oxford, Ashmolean Museum of Art and Archaeology at Oxford, England.
Moved 2001 to University of Oxford, Sackler Library at Oxford, England.

msIdentifier.msName: P. Oxy. 4402, University of Oxford, Sackler Library, Oxford, England.

sourceDesc.bibl: Thomas, J. David, The Oxyrhynchus Papyri, vol. 64, no. 4401, Egypt Exploration Society: London, England, 1997. OCLC 855777953.
